						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Water/Related-developments/Fertilisers-provide-mixed-benefits-to-soil-in-50-year-study" title="Fertilisers provide mixed benefits to soil in 50-year study" alt="link">Fertilisers provide mixed benefits to soil in 50-year study</a></h2>

	
					<p>While 50 years of inorganic fertilization did increase soil organic carbon stocks in a long-term experiment in western Kansas, the practice seemingly failed to enhance soil aggregate stability – a key indicator of soil structural quality that helps dictate how water moves through soil and soil's resistance to erosion.(via <a href="http://www.eurekalert.org/pub_releases/2013-04/asoa-fpm042613.php " target="_blank">Eurekalert</a>, 29/04/2013)</p>
							<p><span class="date">27/06/2013</span></p>
