						<p><div class="item">
<h2><a class="listing" style="link" href="/en/Dossiers/S-T-Issues/Water/Related-developments/Tools-to-improve-water-quality-in-agricultural-landscapes" title="Tools to improve water quality in agricultural landscapes" alt="link">Tools to improve water quality in agricultural landscapes</a></h2>

	
					<p>Cy Jones, People and Ecosystems expert at the World Resources Institute (WRI), has produced an overview of the tools available to help control nutrient pollution in water systems.&nbsp; Explaining how technical assistance programmes for agriculture can help, the author also details policy instruments that are relevant in this context: regulatory requirements, agricultural taxes and fees, environmental cross-compliance, water quality trading programmes and green payments to farmers. The post has several links to relevant resources documenting the water pollution caused by agriculture.(<a href="http://insights.wri.org/news/2012/08/tools-improve-water-quality" target="_blank">WRI Insights</a>, 29/8/2012)</p>
							<p><span class="date">23/10/2012</span></p>
	<div class="cnt">
